-- Albania could borrow up to 500 mln euros in Eurobond or syndicated loan next year - finmin
-- By Michael Shields
-- Tue Jun 03, 2014 06:40AM EDT
-- None



VIENNA, June 3 (Reuters) - Albania could borrow up to 500 million euros ($680 million) in a Eurobond or syndicated loan next year, depending on the mood of the market, Finance Minister Shkelqim Cani said on Tuesday.

Speaking to Reuters on the sidelines of an finance conference in Vienna, Cani said the Adriatic nation had "many options" from which to chose and had started initial talks to sound out potential investors.